{"parse":{"title":"cabbage","pageid":42226,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n{{wp}}\n[[File:Cabbage field, Small Lane North, Halsall - geograph.org.uk - 4708757.jpg|thumb|A cabbage field in Lancashire]]\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈkæbɪd͡ʒ/|a=RP,GA,CA,AU}}\n** {{audio|en|En-us-cabbage.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈkabɪd͡ʒ/|a=SSB,Northern England,Scotland,Wales}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-cabbage.ogg|a=SSB}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈkɛbəd͡ʒ/|a=NZ}}\n* Homophones: [[CABG]] (one pronunciation)\n* {{hyph|en|cab|bage}}\n* {{rhymes|en|æbɪdʒ|s=2}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|en|id=vegetable|:inh|enm:caboche|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|caboche|caboche, cabage|cabbage”; “a certain fish}}, a borrowing from {{der|en|xno|-}}<ref name=\"Dict\">{{R:Dictionary.com}}</ref><ref name=\"AHD\">{{R:American Heritage Dictionary}}</ref> {{m|fro|caboche||head}}, a northern variant of {{m|fro|caboce}},<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=caboche|pos=n|id=MED6439}}</ref> of uncertain origin. Some authorities derive it from {{der|en|la|caput||head}},<ref name=\"AHD\"/> others from {{m|fro||ca-}} (said to be an [[expressive]] prefix) + {{m|fro|boce||hump; bump}} (whence {{m+|en|boss}}).<ref name=\"Dict\"/><ref>{{R:fr:TLFi|caboche|etym=1}}</ref>\n\n====Noun====\n[[Image:Wirsingkohl.jpg|thumb|right|175px|A head of '''cabbage'''.]]\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q35051}}An edible plant ({{taxfmt|Brassica oleracea var. capitata|variety}}) having a [[head]] of green [[leaf|leaves]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1961|author=Harry E. Wedeck|title=Dictionary of Aphrodisiacs|publisher=The Citadel Press|location=New York|page=53|passage=In aphrodisiac preparation, wild '''cabbage''' was frequently an ingredient.}}\n## {{lb|en|by extension}} Any of various [[cultivar]]s of the species {{taxfmt|Brassica oleracea|species}}.\n# {{senseid|en|Q14328596}}{{lb|en|uncountable|vegetable}} The [[leaf|leaves]] of this plant eaten as a [[vegetable]].\n#: {{ux|en|'''Cabbage''' is good for you.}}\n# {{lb|en|countable|offensive}} A person with severely reduced mental capacities due to [[brain damage]].\n#: {{ux|en|After the car crash, he became a '''cabbage'''.}}\n# {{non-gloss|Used as a term of endearment.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=w:The Cherry Orchard|page=31|by=w:Anton Chekhov|author=w:Tom Stoppard; Helen Rappaport|year=2009|year_published=1904|original=[[Вишнëвый сад]] (\"Vishniovy sad\")|passage=If you deceive me, Yasha, I don't know if my nerves could stand it. YASHA (kissing her) My little '''cabbage'''! Of course, a girl must know her place.}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|slang}} Money.\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|slang}} Marijuana leaf, the part that is not smoked but from which [[cannabutter]] can be extracted.\n# A [[terminal]] [[bud]] of certain [[palm tree]]s, used for food.\n# A [[cabbage palmetto]] ({{taxlink|Sabal palmetto|species}}), a palm of the southeastern US coasts and nearby islands.\n# {{lb|en|slang|AAVE}} A human head.\n#* {{quote-song|en|year=2024|artist={{w|JPEGMAFIA |JPEGMAFIA}}|title=Cult Status|passage=American made choppas / You beefin', we split ya '''cabbage'''}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{sense|plant}} cabbage plant, [[cole]]<!--\"cole\" needs checking-->\n* {{sense|leaves of this plant eaten as a vegetable}} {{l|en|cole}}, {{l|en|greens}}<!--\"cole\" needs checking-->\n* {{sense|person with severely reduced mental capacities due to brain damage}} {{l|en|vegetable}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|bacon and cabbage\n|beach cabbage\n|cabbage aphid\n|cabbageball\n|cabbage-bark\n|cabbage butterfly\n|cabbage fly\n|cabbage gum\n|cabbagehead,cabbage head,cabbage-head\n|cabbageless\n|cabbage lettuce\n|cabbagelike\n|cabbage looper\n|cabbage moth\n|cabbage on a stick\n|cabbage palm\n|cabbage patch\n|cabbage roll\n|cabbage root fly\n|cabbage rose\n|cabbage salad\n|Cabbagetown\n|Cabbage Tree\n|Cabbage Tree Island\n|cabbage white\n|cabbagewood\n|cabbage worm\n|cabbagy\n|celery cabbage\n|cone cabbage\n|drumhead cabbage\n|green mustard cabbage\n|harlequin cabbage bug\n|hispi cabbage\n|how the cow ate the cabbage\n|I don't boil my cabbage twice\n|I don't chew my cabbage twice\n|imported cabbage worm\n|jazz cabbage\n|kaffir cabbage\n|Kerguelen cabbage\n|Liberty cabbage,liberty cabbage\n|Lundy cabbage\n|Milan cabbage\n|mountain cabbage\n|napa cabbage\n|Nile cabbage\n|not as green as one is cabbage-looking\n|palm cabbage\n|pointed cabbage\n|poor man's cabbage\n|Savoy cabbage\n|sea cabbage\n|sea otter's cabbage\n|skunk cabbage\n|St Patrick's cabbage\n|sugarloaf cabbage\n|sweetheart cabbage\n|thousand-headed cabbage\n|turnip-cabbage\n|wallflower cabbage\n|warrigal cabbage\n|water cabbage\n|white cabbage\n|wild cabbage\n}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|srn|kabisi}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|abe|kabij}}\n* {{desc|sm|kapisi|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sw|kabichi|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|yo|kábéèjì|bor=1}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|specific cultivar}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|مَلْفُوف|m}}, {{t|ar|كُرُنْب|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|كرنب|m-p|tr=kurumb}}\n*: Gulf Arabic: {{t|afb|مَلْفُوف|tr=malfūf}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|كُرُنْب|m-p|tr=kurunb}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{t|ary|مكور|tr=mkawwar}}\n*: North Levantine Arabic: {{t|ajp|مَلْفُوف|tr=malfūf}}\n*: South Levantine Arabic: {{t|ajp|مَلْفُوف|tr=malfūf}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|aza}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{t+|bcl|repolyo}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|ဂေါ်ဖီထုပ်}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|椰菜|tr=je4 coi3}}\n*: Dungan: {{t|dng|лянхуабый}}\n*: Hokkien: {{t|nan-hbl|高麗菜|tr=ko-lê-chhài}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|捲心菜|tr=juǎnxīncài}}, {{t+|cmn|高麗菜|tr=gāolícài}}, {{t+|cmn|洋白菜|tr=yángbáicài}}, {{t+|cmn|包心菜|tr=bāoxīncài}}, {{t+|cmn|結球甘藍|tr=jiéqiú gānlán}}, {{t|cmn|疙瘩白|tr=gēdabái}}, {{t+|cmn|包菜|tr=bāocài}}, {{t+|cmn|圓白菜|tr=yuánbáicài}}, {{t+|cmn|蓮花白|tr=liánhuābái}}\n*: Wu: {{t|wuu|捲心菜}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|keräkaali}}, {{t+|fi|kaali}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|repolo|m}}\n* German: {{t|de|Kopfkohl|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|λάχανο|n}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|पत्ता गोभी|f}}, {{t|hi|बंद गोभी|f}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|keräkapusta}}\n* Italian